obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10736)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10736&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Salaries and Allowances of`
  line `Officers of Parliament Act, 1953.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the first day of May, 1953`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10737)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10737&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act "officer of Parliament" means any of the following officers, namely, the`
  line `Chairman and Deputy Chairman of the Council of States and the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the`
  line `House of the People.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10738)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Salaries, etc., of officers of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10738&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Salaries, etc., of officers of Parliament.--^2[(1) There shall be paid to the Chairman of the`
  line `Council of States a salary of ^3[ four lakh rupees] per mensem.]`
  line
  line `(2) Each officer of Parliament, other than the Chairman of the Council of States, shall be entitled to`
  line `receive a salary per mensem and an allowance for each day during the whole of his term as such officer at`
  line `the same rates as are specified in section 3 of the Salaries, Allowances and Pension of Members of`
  line `Parliament Act, 1954 (30 of 1954) with respect to members of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(3) Each officer of Parliament, other than the Chairman of the Council of States, shall be entitled to`
  line `receive a constituency allowance at the same rate as is specified under section 8 of the said Act with`
  line `respect to members of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 75 of 1985, s. 2, for section 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1998, s. 2 for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 140, for "one lakh twenty-five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10739)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Residence for officers of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10739&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Each officer of Parliament shall be entitled without`
  line `payment of rent to the use of a furnished residence throughout his term of office and for a period of ^2[one`
  line `month] immediately thereafter, and no charge shall fall on the officer personally in respect of the`
  line `maintenance of such residence.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) In the event of the death of an officer of Parliament, his family shall be entitled to the use of the`
  line `furnished residence occupied by the officer of Parliament--`
  line
  line `(a) for a period of one month immediately after his death, without payment of rent and no charge`
  line `shall fall on the family of the officer of Parliament in respect of the maintenance of such residence,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) for a further period of one month, on payment of rent at such rates as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules made in this behalf under section 11 and also charges in respect of electricity and water`
  line `consumed in that residence during such further period.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "residence" includes the staff quarters and other`
  line `buildings appurtenant thereto and the garden thereof, and "maintenance" in relation to a residence`
  line `includes the payment of local rates and taxes and the provision of electricity and water.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 4 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 49 of 1970, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "fifteen days" (w.e.f. 1-11-1969).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10740)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Sumptuary allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10740&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Sumptuary allowance.--There shall be paid to ^2*** the Speaker of the House of the People a`
  line `sumptuary allowance of one thousand rupees per mensem and to the Deputy Chairman and the Deputy`
  line `Speaker a sumptuary allowance of five hundred rupees per mensem:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that on and from the 17th day of September, 2001, the sumptuary allowance shall be paid`
  line to--
  line
  line `(a) the Speaker of the House of the People at the same rate at which the sumptuary allowance is`
  line `payable, under section 5 of the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952 (58 of 1952), to every`
  line `other Minister who is a member of the Cabinet;`
  line
  line `(b) the Deputy Chairman and the Deputy Speaker at the same rate at which the sumptuary`
  line `allowance is payable, under section 5 of the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952`
  line `(58 of 1952), to a Minister of State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 75 of 1985, s. 3, for section 5 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. The words "the Chairman of the Council of States and" omitted by Act 26 of 1998, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 2002, s. 2 (w.e.f. 17-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10741)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Travelling and daily allowances to officers of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 2002, s. 2, for sub-section (1A) (w.e.f. 17-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10741&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in this`
  line `behalf under section 11, an officer of Parliament shall be entitled to--`
  line
  line `(a) travelling allowances for himself and the members of his family and for the transport of his`
  line `and his family's effects--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of the journey to Delhi from his usual place of residence outside Delhi for`
  line `assuming office, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of the journey from Delhi to his usual place of residence outside Delhi on`
  line `relinquishing office; and`
  line
  line `(b) travelling and daily allowances in respect of tours undertaken by him in the discharge of his`
  line `official duties, whether by sea, land or air.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) On and from the commencement of the Salaries and Allowances of Officers of Parliament`
  line `and Leaders of Opposition in Parliament (Second Amendment) Act, 2002 (56 of 2002), an officer of`
  line `Parliament and his family, whether travelling together or separately, shall be entitled to travelling`
  line `allowance at the same rates and for the same number of return journeys as admissible to a Minister`
  line `and his family under sub-section (1A) of section 6 of the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act,`
  line `1952 (58 of 1952).]`
  line
  line `(2) Any travelling allowance under this section may be paid in cash or free official transport may be`
  line `provided in lieu thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10742)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Medical facilities to officers of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10742&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf under`
  line `section 11, an officer of Parliament and the members of his family shall be entitled free of charge to`
  line `accommodation in hospitals maintained by the Government and also to medical treatment.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (10743)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Family pension, etc., to spouse of Speaker dying in office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2002, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-3-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10743&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Family pension, etc., to spouse of Speaker dying in office.--(1) With effect from the`
  line `commencement of the Salaries and Allowances of Officers of Parliament (Second Amendment) Act, 2002`
  line `(31 of 2002), there shall be paid a family pension, to the spouse of the Speaker of the House of the People`
  line `who dies while holding such office at the rate of fifty per cent. of the salary last drawn by him for the`
  line `remainder of life of such spouse from the date of death of the Speaker:`
  line
  line `Provided that the spouse of such Speaker shall not be entitled to receive pension available to the`
  line `spouse of any member of Parliament who dies during his term of office as such member for a period of`
  line `five years from the date of death of the member under sub-section (1A) of section 8A of the Salary,`
  line `Allowances and Pension of Members of Parliament Act, 1954 (30 of 1954).`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4 and subject to any`
  line `rules made in this behalf under section 11, such spouse shall be entitled to the use of unfurnished`
  line `residence without payment of licence fee for the remainder of her life.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to any rules made in this behalf under section 11,--`
  line
  line `(a) such spouse, for the remainder of her life; and`
  line
  line `(b) the minor children of such Speaker,`
  line
  line `shall be entitled to medical attendance and treatment, free of charge.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10744)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Advances to officers of Parliament for purchase of motor-cars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10744&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `There may be paid to any`
  line `officer of Parliament by way of a repayable advance such sum of money as may be determined by rules`
  line `made in this behalf under section 11 for the purchase of a motor-car in order that he may be able to`
  line `discharge conveniently and efficiently the duties of his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10745)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers of Parliament not to draw salary or allowances as Members of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10745&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line No
  line `officer of Parliament in receipt of a salary or allowance under this Act shall be entitled to receive any sum`
  line `out of funds provided by Parliament by way of salary or allowance in respect of his membership of either`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10746)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Notification respecting appointment, etc., of officers of Parliament to be conclusive evidence thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10746&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The date on which any person became or ceased to be an officer of Parliament shall be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette and any such notification shall be conclusive evidence of the fact that he`
  line `became, or ceased to be, an officer of Parliament on that date for all the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (10747)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 12
  title `Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on daily allowance received by the Chairman and certain perquisites received by an officer of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 1990, s. 3, for section 10A (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10747&sectionno=10A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on daily allowance received by the Chairman`
  line `and certain perquisites received by an officer of Parliament.--Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961),--`
  line
  line `(a) in computing the total income of a previous year of the Chairman of the Council of States, any`
  line `income by way of an allowance referred to in sub-section (1) of section 3 shall not be included;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of rent free furnished residence (including maintenance thereof) provided to an`
  line `officer of Parliament under sub-section (1) of section 4 shall not be included in the computation of his`
  line `income chargeable under the head "Salaries" under section 15 of the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10748)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417&sectionId=10748&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00007_195320_1517807328417
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Chairman and`
  line `the Speaker, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
